1
00:00:05,238 --> 00:00:06,538
I didn't expect

2
00:00:06,539 --> 00:00:07,840
you to step up for me today.

3
00:00:07,841 --> 00:00:08,841
Please.

4
00:00:08,842 --> 00:00:10,043
In front of my fans,

5
00:00:10,410 --> 00:00:11,011
if I didn't have your back,

6
00:00:11,012 --> 00:00:12,278
what kind of man would I be?

7
00:00:15,915 --> 00:00:17,183
You don't have to thank me.

8
00:00:17,751 --> 00:00:18,718
Like I said,

9
00:00:18,719 --> 00:00:20,120
I really want us to be friends.

10
00:00:26,993 --> 00:00:28,128
Just friends?

11
00:00:30,230 --> 00:00:31,931
Don't push your luck.

12
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:35,902
I offered to cook for you,

13
00:00:36,503 --> 00:00:38,338
and you asked for instant noodles?

14
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:42,861
I thought you didn't like onions.

15
00:00:43,743 --> 00:00:46,011
But you said without them,

16
00:00:46,012 --> 00:00:47,013
it's just not the same.

17
00:00:53,953 --> 00:00:55,087
When I was a kid,

18
00:00:55,088 --> 00:00:56,528
my parents wouldn't let me eat this.

19
00:00:57,891 --> 00:00:59,058
So I used to go online

20
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:00,760
and play "blind eating" with someone.

21
00:01:01,494 --> 00:01:03,196
Do you know what that is?

22
00:01:05,331 --> 00:01:07,500
We'd guess the ingredients,

23
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:09,201
then "cook" using only words,

24
00:01:09,202 --> 00:01:11,036
and finally reveal the dish.

25
00:01:11,037 --> 00:01:12,072
How did you know?

26
00:01:12,705 --> 00:01:14,641
Was that a popular game?

27
00:01:15,675 --> 00:01:16,342
I thought it was just

28
00:01:16,343 --> 00:01:18,011
something me and that friend did.

29
00:01:21,314 --> 00:01:22,315
An online friend?

30
00:01:23,116 --> 00:01:24,217
Are you still in touch?

31
00:01:24,617 --> 00:01:25,785
No, not for a long time.

32
00:01:27,153 --> 00:01:27,720
Years ago,

33
00:01:27,721 --> 00:01:30,156
my nephew messed with my phone

34
00:01:30,890 --> 00:01:31,491
and got the password wrong.

35
00:01:31,492 --> 00:01:33,059
It was locked forever.

36
00:01:33,293 --> 00:01:35,527
I got some contacts back,

37
00:01:35,528 --> 00:01:37,563
but others were gone forever.

38
00:01:37,564 --> 00:01:38,564
He was one of them.

39
00:01:40,967 --> 00:01:42,634
Maybe that's why

40
00:01:42,635 --> 00:01:43,670
I'm feeling so nostalgic.

41
00:01:44,504 --> 00:01:46,439
It's a shame A-You and Youzhi

42
00:01:46,739 --> 00:01:47,739
split up without closure.

43
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:49,041
It's a real pity.

44
00:01:49,976 --> 00:01:50,976
Yeah.

45
00:01:51,211 --> 00:01:52,979
We're filming the finale tomorrow.

46
00:01:53,446 --> 00:01:55,248
Did the director say how it ends?

47
00:01:58,060 --> 00:01:59,194
That's enough.

48
00:01:59,219 --> 00:02:00,619
He said we'll discuss it tomorrow.

49
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:01,620
Now, go home.

50
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:06,191
Why don't we go together tomorrow?

51
00:02:06,192 --> 00:02:07,994
You live so close to the set.

52
00:02:09,095 --> 00:02:10,497
I won't be able to sleep otherwise.

53
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:12,764
But I can't bear to leave you,

54
00:02:12,765 --> 00:02:14,634
Little You-You.

55
00:02:15,068 --> 00:02:16,202
I'm not A-You.

56
00:02:16,836 --> 00:02:18,104
Little Yan-Yan.

57
00:02:18,371 --> 00:02:19,738
Big Brother Yan.

58
00:02:19,739 --> 00:02:20,739
Oppa.
